summary: Richard C. Nagell is connected to the case of Victor L. Trinkala, a soldier who sought separation from military service as a conscientious objector. Nagell appears to have intervened to prevent Trinkala's deployment to Vietnam. An agent report also details a local agency check on Post Office Box 2337, registered to Richard C. Nagell at 2292 Edythe Drive, Dundeon, Florida. Harfez Muneer was interviewed regarding Nagell's connections to Trinkala's separation from military service.
significance: The significance of Richard C. Nagell in the JFK context is not explicitly stated in these documents. However, his involvement in preventing Victor L. Trinkala's deployment to Vietnam and the investigation into his post office box suggest potential connections to anti-war or subversive activities during that period. Further research would be needed to determine his relevance to the JFK assassination.
